title: Grateful Dead Live at Henry J Kaiser Convention Center on 1987-11-07
description:
Set 1

Hey Pocky Way, Jack Straw, Row Jimmy, When I Paint My Masterpiece, Dupree's Diamond Blues, Box Of Rain-> Cassidy-> Might As Well

Set 2

Uncle John's Band-> Playin' In The Band-> Terrapin Station-> Drums-> Jam-> I Need A Miracle-> Black Peter-> Throwing Stones-> Not Fade Away, E:Not Fade Away-> E: Knockin' On Heaven's Door, E: One More Saturday Night

Rex Benefit *Lights went on, crowd wouldn't leave.Band came back played OMSN, "We Want Phil Chant before Box

reviews.review_text: Prelude? Good Quality !!!! THIS. This show is one of my favorites and probably most never would bother. BUT this quality is way betterthan the versions I have had since 11/8/87, and I thank you. Is that Prelude from 73/ What is it?I'll  listen and see. whocares this show rocks and this is an improvement in quality, but they all sound muddy. Does the bandhave better ones cause its the same with a lot from those days. Out of maybe 150 shows I probably caught five or ten Duprees. This oneis vewy vewy good.
